SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1349
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR BROWN (26).
5044S.02I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 324, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to a prohibition on
licensing requirements for certain industrial mechanical maintenance work.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 324, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 324.890, to read as
3 follows:
1 324.890. 1. As used in this section, the following
2 terms mean:
3 (1) "Contractor", a person who is employed by a
4 corporation, firm, institution, organization, or company to
5 perform industrial mechanical maintenance work;
6 (2) "Establishment", any legally recognized business
7 entity engaged in manufacturing;
8 (3) "Industrial facility", any real property or
9 personal property or fixtures attached to real property at
10 which an establishment engages in a manufacturing activity
11 within an area that, if subject to a zoning ordinance or
12 regulation, is zoned for industrial or similar uses;
13 (4) "Industrial mechanical maintenance work",
14 maintenance of mechanical systems or equipment within an
15 industrial facility;
16 (5) "Local license", a license issued by a political
17 subdivision and valid only in that political subdivision

SB 1349 2
18 that is required to bid, accept, or perform mechanical work
19 in a political subdivision of this state;
20 (6) "Manufacturing", any activity described in
21 division D of the most recent version of the Standard
22 Industrial Classification Manual;
23 (7) "State license", a license issued by the state of
24 Missouri that is required to bid, accept, or perform
25 mechanical work in this state.
26 2. Any contractor performing industrial mechanical
27 maintenance work employed at an industrial facility shall
28 not be required to obtain a local license or state license
29 to perform industrial mechanical maintenance work for the
30 industrial facility.
